Dr Horner, a retired doctor who now lives in Newtown, Philadelphia, was 21 when he was freed by Allied soldiers in 1945 after serving time at Terezin, Auschwitz and Buchenwald.

His parents and sister perished in the camps.

Although his back still bears the scars of a Nazi beating, he remains sprightly and seems much younger than his 90 years.

Ma, who was born 10 years after the end of the Second World War, said before the performance that he hoped it will inspire people to a better future.

