Horner played piano and accordion in the Terezin cabarets, including tunes written by fellow inmate Karel Svenk.

Last night Horner played two of Svenk's works solo — a march and a lullaby — and then teamed up with Ma for a third piece called 'How Come the Black Man Sits in the Back of the Bus?'

